to her grandfather's' during Roger's final illness in early 1683."},{"number":3,"category":"death","header":"May 1699 deposition: widow Lydia and four children","body":"He died in May 1699 in Milford. Lydia's deposition for the May 18 estate inventory survives, listing their children — Prudence about 18, Thomas about 17, Ezekiel, and John about 2. She was 38 and a widow with four to raise."},{"number":4,"category":"family","header":"Lydia Ford lived 48 years a widow","body":"Lydia Ford remained a widow until her death in 1747 at age 86 — 48 years after John's death. Milford Land Records show numerous transactions in her name, and her 1746 will divided the estate among her surviving children and grandchildren."}],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"artworks":[],"bio":{"display_name":"John Newton","first_name":"John","last_name":"Newton","married_names":[]},"documents":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"john-newton-1656"},"I00012":{"id":"I00012","classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"is_progenitor":false},"birth":{"year":1661,"month":3,"day":15,"city":"Milford","county":"New Haven County","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1747,"month":10,"day":23,"city":"Milford","county":"New Haven County","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM005"},"parents":{"father_id":"X00012","mother_id":"X00013"},"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"H00014","children_ids":["H00055","H00042","H00057","H00059","X00012"],"marriage_number":1,"end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1699,"date_year":1680,"date_month":4,"date_day":14}],"tags":[],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909","page":"Entry 14"},{"short":"Ford Genealogy 1916","full":"Eliakim Reed Ford, Ford Genealogy (Oneonta, N.Y.: E.R. Ford, 1916), p. 15"},{"short":"Jacobus 1976","full":"Donald Lines Jacobus, History and Genealogy of the Families of Old Fairfield (Baltimore: Genealogical Publishing Co., 1976), p. 368"}],"gender":"female","number_of_marriages":1,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"is_placeholder":false,"former_ids":[],"baptism":{},"residence":{"country":"United States"},"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"research_tags":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Widowed at 37 — outlived John by 48 years","body":"John Newton died in May 1699, leaving Lydia with five children — the youngest barely two years old. She lived as a widow in Milford until October 23, 1747, dying at roughly age eighty-five after forty-eight years on her own."}],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"artworks":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Lydia Ford Newton","first_name":"Lydia","last_name":"Newton","married_names":["Newton"],"maiden_name":"Ford"},"documents":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"lydia-ford-1661"},"X00019":{"id":"X00019","classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1660,"month":9,"day":22,"city":"Milford","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1722,"month":5,"day":31,"city":"Milford","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"X00024","date_year":1679,"location_city":"Milford","location_county":"New Haven","location_state":"Connecticut","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1691,"children_ids":["I00022"]},{"marriage_number":2,"spouse_id":"X00020","date_year":1689,"location_city":"Milford","location_county":"New Haven","location_state":"Connecticut","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1722,"children_ids":["I00019"]}],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909","page":"Entries 42, 54"}],"gender":"male","tags":["politician","king_philips_war"],"number_of_marriages":2,"parents":{},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"politics","header":"Town Auditor, then fourteen sessions as Representative","body":"Zachariah Baldwin served as Auditor for the town of Milford in 1696, then as Representative in the Connecticut General Assembly for fourteen sessions between 1705 and 1718 — one of the more sustained civic careers among the Milford founding families' descendants."},{"number":2,"category":"religion","header":"Admitted to full communion","body":"In 1693, Zachariah and his second wife Elizabeth were admitted to full communion at First Congregational Church in Milford — the record noting that Zachariah was admitted \"having been forgiven in some unstated context.\" Whatever the transgression, it was significant enough to be recorded, and forgiven enough to be moved past."},{"number":3,"category":"military","header":"The Sergeant title — but which war?","body":"He is styled Sergt. in Milford records throughout his life. Born in 1660, he was 15 during King Philips War (1675-76) — possible but young; he was 29-37 during King Williams War (1689-97), the more likely conflict. The specific service remains unconfirmed in surviving records."}],"cross_connections":[{"type":"family_connection","related_id":"H00042","display_label":"Married my daughter Mary; his cousin married my daughter Susanna","link_text":"Thomas Newton"},{"type":"family_connection","related_id":"H00054","display_label":"Both Hooker-line grandsons married his daughters","link_text":"John Burwell"}],"military_service":[{"war":"King Williams War (probable) or King Philips War (possible)","rank":"Sergeant","side":"Colonial","battles":[]}],"bio":{"title":"Sergeant","display_name":"Sgt. Zachariah Baldwin","first_name":"Zachariah","last_name":"Baldwin","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"slug":"zachariah-baldwin-1660"},"X00024":{"id":"X00024","classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1652,"month":5,"day":14,"city":"New Haven","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1691,"city":"Milford","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"X00019","date_year":1679,"location_city":"Milford","location_county":"New Haven","location_state":"Connecticut","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1691,"children_ids":["I00022"]}],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909","page":"Entry 42"}],"parents":{"father_id":"X02113","father_name":"Luke Atkinson","mother_id":"X02114","mother_name":"Mary Platt Atkinson"},"cross_connections":[],"gender":"female","tags":[],"number_of_marriages":1,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Granddaughter of Deacon Richard Platt, Milford founding settler","body":"Her mother Mary was a daughter of Deacon Richard Platt — one of the 66 founding members of the Milford church in 1639, who came from Hertfordshire with Rev. Peter Prudden's company in 1638. Through her mother's line, Mary Atkinson Baldwin carried the bloodline of one of colonial Connecticut's foundational families."}],"bio":{"display_name":"Mary Atkinson Baldwin","first_name":"Mary","last_name":"Baldwin","married_names":["Baldwin"],"maiden_name":"Atkinson"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"mary-atkinson-1652"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}